    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not about finding something new. that's the thing. there's nothing left to replace. when i look back at the person i was supposed to be, it feels like looking at a different species. i'm just existing in this shell of a life that doesn't belong to me anymore. it feels so heavy, carrying around a body that's just a tomb for everything i lost.",
